          <h2>Lessons 1 &amp; 2: Glucose Homeostasis — Dry Run Submission</h2>

          <p class="section-intro">
            This is your time to <strong>finish and submit</strong> the dry run for your glucose
            homeostasis report (AS 91604). These two lessons are dedicated work time — use them
            wisely. You have been building the knowledge for this since Week 7, and you have
            everything you need to write a strong response.
          </p>

          <!-- Motivational callout -->
          <div class="encouragement-box">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M12 2L15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
            <div>
              <strong>You can do this.</strong> This is a dry run — it is your chance to practise
              before the real assessment. Treat it seriously, get detailed feedback, and your final
              submission will be much stronger for it. Give it your best effort now so you know
              exactly where to improve.
            </div>
          </div>


          <!-- ── Deadline Reminder ── -->
          <div class="deadline-box">
            <div class="deadline-box__icon">
              <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <path d="M12 6v6l4 2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <strong>Submission Deadline</strong>
              <span class="deadline-box__date">Tuesday 25 March 2025, 23:59</span>
              <p>Submit your dry run by the end of the day. Late submissions will not receive
              feedback before the final assessment window opens.</p>
            </div>
          </div>


          <!-- ── What to Do ── -->
          <h3>What Should You Be Doing?</h3>

          <p>
            You should be writing (or finalising) your dry run report. This report should explain
            how the body maintains a stable blood glucose concentration, using the homeostatic
            framework you learned in Weeks 7 and 8. If you are stuck, review the reference
            material from those weeks — links are in the sidebar.
          </p>

          <div class="action-steps">
            <div class="action-step">
              <div class="action-step__number">1</div>
              <div class="action-step__content">
                <strong>Review your notes</strong> — make sure you understand the full negative
                feedback loop (stimulus, receptor, control centre, effector, response, feedback).
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="action-step">
              <div class="action-step__number">2</div>
              <div class="action-step__content">
                <strong>Write or complete your draft</strong> — use the checklist below to make
                sure you have not missed anything important.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="action-step">
              <div class="action-step__number">3</div>
              <div class="action-step__content">
                <strong>Proofread and submit</strong> — read it through once, check your
                biological terminology, and submit before the deadline.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>


        <!-- ——————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————
             Submission Checklist
             —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— -->
        <section id="checklist" class="content-section fade-in-up">
          <h2>Dry Run Checklist</h2>

          <p class="section-intro">
            Use this checklist to make sure your report covers all the key components. Tick
            each item off as you confirm it is addressed in your writing.
          </p>

          <div class="checklist-group">
            <h3>Core Content (Achieved)</h3>
            <ul class="checklist">
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Normal blood glucose set point identified (~5 mmol/L fasting)</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Role of insulin described (lowers blood glucose)</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Role of glucagon described (raises blood glucose)</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Pancreas identified as the control centre (islets of Langerhans)</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Negative feedback loop described in general terms</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>At least one example of disruption mentioned (e.g. diabetes)</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="checklist-group">
            <h3>Depth &amp; Detail (Merit)</h3>
            <ul class="checklist">
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Beta cells and alpha cells distinguished clearly</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Glycogenesis and glycogenolysis explained (not just named)</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                </svg>
                <span>Insulin signal transduction pathway described (receptor binding, cascade, GLUT4)</span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                  <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="3" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
