          </div>

          <div class="exam-tip">
            <h4>Why This Matters for the Exam</h4>
            <p>
              In the AS 91603 external exam, you will need to describe and explain animal
              behaviours using real examples. Building a bank of vivid, well-understood examples
              from documentaries like Our Planet gives you concrete material to draw on. The
              best exam answers use specific examples — not vague generalisations.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="connection-box">
            <h4>Connecting Back to Earlier Weeks</h4>
            <p>
              The behaviours you observe in this episode connect directly to the concepts you
              studied in Weeks 3–6: taxis, kinesis, innate vs learned behaviour, orientation,
              and navigation. As you watch, think about which category each behaviour fits
              into. This is revision <em>and</em> new learning at the same time.
            </p>
          </div>
